The paper discusses a security protocol for the Internet of Things (IoT), which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The protocol is designed to be scalable and suitable for all IoT devices, which suggests a focus on system-level design and engineering (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper evaluates the protocol's performance in terms of memory footprint and runtime, indicating a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC).
